  "body": "<!-- Have you done the following? -->\r\n<!--   * read the Code of Conduct? By filing an Issue, you are expected to -->  \r\n<!--     comply with it, including treating everyone with respect: -->\r\n<!--     https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/blob/main/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md -->\r\n<!--   * Reproduced the issue in the latest version of the software -->\r\n<!--   * Read the debugging docs: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Monitor/Logging/ -->\r\n<!--   * Duplicate Issue check:  https://github.com/search?q=+is%3Aissue+repo%3Ahyperledger/Besu -->\r\n<!-- Note:  Not all sections will apply to all issue types. -->\r\n\r\n### Description\r\nThe existing github action which tags the latest docker artifacts in dockerhub appears to be broken.  After the release of 23.7.1, the `latest` tags for all variants were pointing to 23.1.3.  It is less clear if the github action updated the tags to 23.1.3 or whether they hadn't been updated since the original release of 23.1.3\r\n\r\nSee this discord thread for additional details:\r\nhttps://discord.com/channels/905194001349627914/1143574070974218260\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Upon publishing of a release on github, the corresponding variants' versions get tagged as `latest` in dockerhub\r\n* manifest metadata is pushed for the `latest` such that `latest` tags are both amd64 and arm64\r\n\r\n",
